lead_paragraph: LEAD: The scheduled death of Robert Alton Harris in the gas chamber here, the first state killing in California in nearly a quarter of a century, will not merely be No. 122 in a string of executions since the United States Supreme Court reinstated capital punishment in 1976.

headline.main: Question Arises as Execution Nears: Would California Death Be a Signal?

byline.original: By JANE GROSS, Special to The New York Times
